&quot;Really?  What does it say Yshaa?&quot;<br>
&quot;Hm, it is written in Tier'Dal, what a surprise to find another memoir of the past in Befallen.&quot;<br>
&quot;Well, read it!&quot;<br>
&quot;Yes, of course:<br>
'To whom it may concern:<br>
I am Faalins, messenger of Lady Korlanu.  I have been asked to describe the fate that befell the K'Arlah family.<br>
First off, I am forever to dwell within this tomb as a Elf Skeleton, that is my fate, the process has begun already.<br>
Second, my Lady Korlanu had her sould put in the body of her daughter, Kaylanu who before the fusion had no potential for magic.<br>
Third, the father of the family, his name escapes me for I did not fully escape the affects of the amnesia cast upon us, has been turned to stone and taken away to Innoruuk knows where...<br>
The fate of the last 3 children ws decided by my Lady, Yshaa was already undergoing her training at the spires, I brought Kaylanu to the Lodge of the Dead like I was asked, and Elaisi, fair Elaisi, I brought her to the house of Enchanters, for I felt al three children should take separate paths.<br>
This conspiracy will not be remembered until the king finds the book Korlanu told me about, and it was hidden long ago, this plot cannot go underway until Lanys can be removed from the Plane of hate.  And I know Innoruuk will probably wipe the minds of all who participated in this conspiracy.  Do not let us suffer in vain...find the truth<br>
Long Live the Tier'Dal&quot;'<br>
&quot;That is it?&quot;<br>
&quot;Yes&quot;<br>
&quot;Innoruuk probably found out already...&quot;<br>
&quot;It would seem so..they found the book, but cannot kill Lanys, I certainly hope that this is the last letter though.&quot;<br>
